text:
Although not a massive structure, the building houses a variety of open shops. The interior lacks of light but provides sufficient brightness for the shops.

The range of establishments includes antique stores, a mini-market, small eateries, an amulet shop, and a massage center etc. Access the car park from the road adjacent to Hotel 81.

This place may look, feel, and smell like it's haunted by like seven generations worth of ghosts, but the Vietnamese restaurant on the ground floor serves absolutely divine banh mi and coffee so I don't actually mind it all that much.

Really cool Christopher Nolan Inception esque architecture as well.
Car park gentry is a failure in such a technology country. Not sure is the resident or tenant paying the mcst for. Lousy car park n lifts canâ€™t be used to go from carpark to level 2.

I only patronized the durian stall outside
